# Arkadian LMS (ALMS) — Continuing Development (Session 5)

I'm building Arkadian LMS, a Learning Management System for ARK Technological Institute Education System Inc. Picking up from Session 4.

## 🎯 What was completed in Session 4

### Phase 4 — Student side (the planned work)

**Phase 4 step 1 — Join-by-code modal + `/student/classes` page (verified end-to-end):**
- `src/components/students/JoinClassModal.tsx` (NEW) — code-entry dialog used from both student dashboard and student classes page. Handles three result `kind`s from `requestJoinClassByCode`: `'pending'`, `'already_enrolled'`, `'request_pending'`. Different success messages per branch. Submits via try/catch (matching `enrollments.ts` throw-on-error convention).
- `src/components/students/StudentClassesView.tsx` (NEW) — read-only enrolled-class grid (no 3-dot menu, no edit/archive/delete), pending-requests section with Cancel button per request, "+ Join class" button at top.
- `src/app/(dashboard)/student/classes/page.tsx` (REPLACED placeholder) — server component, calls `listMyEnrolledClasses` + `listMyPendingRequests` in `Promise.all`, hands off to `StudentClassesView`.

**Phase 4 step 2 — Student dashboard:**
- `src/components/students/StudentDashboardView.tsx` (NEW) — client wrapper for the join modal's open state. Two stat cards (Enrolled / Pending), recent classes section with same `RecentClassCard` pattern as teacher dashboard for visual consistency, "+ Join class" button.
- `src/app/(dashboard)/student/dashboard/page.tsx` (REPLACED placeholder) — server component, fetches both lists, slices to top 3 recent classes.

**Phase 4 step 3 — Shareable join link `/join/[code]`:**
- New SQL function `preview_class_by_code(p_code)` — read-only RPC, returns `{ status, class_id, class_name, class_section, class_semester, class_color, teacher_name }`. Status is one of: `valid`, `not_found`, `disabled`, `expired`, `already_enrolled`, `request_pending`. Mirrors `request_join_class_by_code` validation but inserts nothing.
- New enum type `public.join_preview_status` for the status column.
- `src/lib/actions/joinPreview.ts` (NEW) — wrapper for the RPC, throws on auth failure but returns soft statuses as data so the UI can switch on them without try/catch hell.
- `src/components/students/JoinConfirmCard.tsx` (NEW) — client component, shows class name/section/teacher in a colored card with a "Confirm and request to join" button. Submits via `requestJoinClassByCode` and renders success/error inline.
- `src/app/(dashboard)/join/[code]/page.tsx` (NEW) — server page, gates on auth and role, switches on preview status to render one of: confirmation card (valid), already-enrolled InfoCard, pending-request InfoCard, error cards (not_found / disabled / expired), or NonStudentBlocked card (teacher/admin trying to join).
- `src/components/landing/LandingNavbar.tsx` (MODIFIED) — reads `?next=` from current URL via `useSearchParams`, validates it's a relative path (`startsWith('/')`, not `startsWith('//')`), forwards to OAuth `redirectTo` as `?next=<encoded>`.
- `src/app/(auth)/auth/callback/route.ts` (MODIFIED) — reads `next` from search params, validates with `safeNext()` helper (relative paths only, blocks protocol/host injection), redirects to `next` if present, otherwise falls back to role dashboard.
- `src/lib/supabase/middleware.ts` (MODIFIED) — added a special-case block at the top: `if (pathname.startsWith('/join/') && !user)` builds a redirect to `/?next=<pathname+search>` using `searchParams.set()`. **This is the critical fix for the Next.js 16 redirect quirk — see learned constraints below.**

**Phase 4 step 4 — Student class detail `/student/classes/[id]`:**
- `getStudentClassById(classId)` (NEW) added to `src/lib/actions/enrollments.ts` — selects from `class_enrollments` joined to `classes` and `profiles`, scoped to the calling student. Relies on existing RLS (`class_enrollments` SELECT for own rows + `classes_select_enrolled_student` for joined class data). Returns `null` if not enrolled.
- `StudentClassDetail` type and export from `enrollments.ts`.
- `src/app/(dashboard)/student/classes/[id]/page.tsx` (NEW) — server page, validates the route param against a UUID regex BEFORE hitting the DB (otherwise non-UUIDs cause Postgres `invalid input syntax for type uuid` errors), wraps the data fetch in try/catch where any failure silently redirects to `/student/classes`. Tabs: Stream / Modules / Activities / Grades (no Students tab). Read-only header with name, section, semester, teacher name (no invite code visible).

### Bonus work — three Session 3 SQL bugs found and fixed

**These were latent bugs that Session 3 introduced but never tested with real data flows. The Phase 4 student-side work was the first time anything actually exercised these paths end-to-end, which is why they only surfaced now.**

1. **`request_join_class_by_code` — ambiguous `class_id` reference.**
   - Migration: `20260505010000_fix_request_join_class_ambiguity.sql`.
   - Bug: function declared `RETURNS TABLE(class_id uuid, ...)` which creates an output column named `class_id`. Inside the body, `WHERE class_id = v_class.id` collided with that output parameter. Postgres raised `column reference "class_id" is ambiguous`.
   - Fix: qualify all column references in WHERE/USING with table aliases (`ce.class_id`, `cjr.class_id`, etc.).

2. **`is_class_teacher` argument order swapped in three places.**
   - The function signature is `is_class_teacher(p_class_id uuid, p_user_id uuid)` — class first, user second.
   - Five call sites correctly pass class first; three Session 3 call sites passed user first. All three silently returned false → policies/checks always denied teachers.
   - **Migration `20260505020000_fix_class_join_requests_teacher_policies.sql`** — DROP+CREATE the two `class_join_requests` teacher RLS policies (`select_teacher`, `update_teacher`) with correct argument order.
   - **Migration `20260505030000_fix_decide_join_request_argument_order.sql`** — `CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION decide_join_request` with corrected `is_class_teacher(v_request.class_id, v_user)` call. (Was raising `'not authorized'` on every Approve/Reject click.)
   - **Migration `20260505040000_fix_regenerate_class_invite_code_argument_order.sql`** — same fix for `regenerate_class_invite_code`. (Reset Code button was broken too; not noticed in Phase 3b verification because reset wasn't actually clicked.)
   - These bugs were 100% invisible in Phase 3a/3b verification because Phase 3 didn't have student-side flows to trigger teacher-side reactions.

### Bonus work — Next.js 16 redirect query-string drop

- **Discovery:** `redirect()` from `next/navigation` strips query strings from the Location header in Next.js 16 + Turbopack. Verified with curl: `redirect('/?foo=bar')` produces `location: /` with no query. This affects every `redirect()` call across the app.
- **Workaround applied for `/join/[code]`:** the auth-gate redirect was moved from the page (`redirect('/?next=...')`) up into middleware (`NextResponse.redirect()` with `searchParams.set()`), which preserves query strings correctly.
- **Page still has its `if (!user) redirect(...)` block** as a defensive fallback if middleware ever stops firing — but it's effectively unreachable.
- **Other redirects in the codebase that use query params should be audited** if/when they're added. Current `redirect()` calls elsewhere only use path-only redirects (e.g. `/student/classes`, `/teacher/dashboard`), so they're fine.

